    "Body": " IT Systems Manager Vermont Foodbank - 4.0 Barre, VT Quick Apply Job Details Full-time$70,000 a year Qualifications IT Experience Virtualization HRIS Computer Skills Computer Hardware Associate's Degree Bachelor's Degree Full Job Description Client: Vermont Foodbank Position Title: IT Systems Manager Reports To: Director of Equity, People & Culture Location: Barre, Vermont About Vermont Foodbank: The mission of the Vermont Foodbank is to gather and share quality food and nurture partnerships so that no one in Vermont will go hungry. The Vermont Foodbank serves over 153,000 Vermonters each year. They work with over 215 network and agency partners to provide nutritious food in each county in the state. The Vermont Foodbank opened its doors in 1986, and is based in Barre, Vermont, with additional warehouse locations in Rutland and Brattleboro. The full and part-time staff is aided by the help of thousands of volunteers in our community. Volunteers are individuals and groups that dedicate their time to making a difference right here in Vermont. Together, with their help, the Vermont Foodbank is able to sort, source, pack and distribute over 12 million pounds of food each year to our network to reach all corners of our state. Position Overview: This position is responsible for overseeing all Information Technology operations, systems (including applications), vendors and consultants for Vermont Foodbank. This will include developing new IT strategies, maintaining the company\u2019s information security program, and ensuring smooth delivery and operation of IT services and performance. This position is responsible for technology that is hosted on-site across our three locations and cloud hosted systems, mobile services and devices, laptops and desktops, planning and managing implementation of new technology products and upgrades to existing hardware and software, and for managing the Foodbank\u2019s relationship with Feeding America, their outsource vendor for technology systems. A high level of internal customer service is essential. Essential Duties and Responsibilities: Works cooperatively and be able to communicate with staff and volunteers to support the mission of the Foodbank to meet and sustain Foodbank goals. Positively contribute to an organizational culture of safe and secure food handling, warehousing and distribution. The Foodbank relies on volunteers every day to fulfill our mission. All Foodbank employees must support our culture of philanthropy by treating every volunteer with appreciation and respect. Provide company-wide strategic leadership regarding IT and security applications and infrastructure, advising Vermont Foodbank\u2019s management team regarding the same. Delivery - Deliver projects, solutions and IT services in support of approved business and technology driven portfolios of work. Deliver solutions that meet functional requirements, meet delivery schedules, within cost projections, and are of high quality. Able to prepare and present IT solution recommendations, status updates, and business value propositions to all levels of the organization and partners. Platform Availability and Stability - Ensure supported IT systems are stable and available. Take action to ensure platforms supported are stable and available. Ensure currency of upgrade path is consistent with IT strategy and business expectations. Plan for capacity, volume growth, retirement, SLA, and OLA's. Business of IT - Leverages Multi-Vendor relationships and ensures high performing vendor deliveries. Collaborates and actively supports other IT functions to ensure overall IT success. Understands IT industry best practices, standards, and resources to ensure continuous optimization of IT delivery effectiveness. Ensure overall success of IT delivery and meet or exceed customer expectations. Comply with process and control requirements. Understand and support Vermont Foodbank\u2019s mission, goals, and priorities. Strategic IT Planning- Interacts with Vermont Foodbank\u2019s leadership to contribute to the IT strategic plan, project portfolio plans, division, department, and individual goals that contribute to the success of the Vermont Foodbank and IT. Be innovative and plan for continuous improvement. Monitor and adjust goals and plan consistent with business and IT leadership expectations. Fulfill vendor management duties which include sourcing vendors, obtaining quotes, managing service levels and quality of work, negotiating contracts, and managing relationships. Serve as liaison between Feeding America and Foodbank staff to triage network and personal computer issues and to ensure timely follow up with technology related tickets. Provide timely support for users of technology at the Foodbank and Network Partners utilizing Foodbank\u2019s software and equipment. Monitor and manage the Foodbank\u2019s IT systems which include computers, networks, internet access, telephone lines, cell phones and other technology. Maintain a 3 to 5-year IT replacement plan so that all equipment is up to date. This will include implementing a plan for repair or replacement of computers and other forms of technology. Provide guidance on technology upgrades and emerging technologies. Provide project management for new technology roll-outs and upgrades. Assist in preparing and managing the technology budget and expenditures to include the purchase of new equipment and software when necessary. Work with management and all departments to implement a successful IT plan. Website Backup: Provide backup support for Website when the primary is not available. Learn how to up load content and provide trouble shooting support when technical issues come up. Be an active leader in IT Steering committee meetings. Other Functions: Serve on applicable Feeding America and Vermont Foodbank committees and discussion groups. Attend regularly scheduled Feeding America follow up meetings. Provide training to all staff on technology related subjects. Work with Equity, People & Culture to deploy computer and information resources for new hires and to deactivate employees in a timely manner. Nurture relationships with equipment manufacturers and service providers. Prepare regular reports for management; attend meetings to present these findings. Visit off-site branches at least monthly for on-site support. Other duties as assigned by the Director of Equity, People & Culture. Qualifications: Proven leadership experience with both information technology and cybersecurity. Demonstrated experience in analysis, implementation and evaluation of IT systems and their specifications. Demonstrated hands-on experience supporting information technology, including hardware, software and systems administration. Demonstrated experience in project management. Demonstrates strong aptitude to work with business owners for planning of organization-wide technologies. Demonstrated experience in IT help desk support. Understanding of basic computer hardware components and possesses skills to repair and replace. Demonstrated experience in a similar direct customer service position. A minimum of an Associate\u2019s Degree, Bachelor\u2019s Degree preferred, in IT or related field. Specialized certification in any of the areas mentioned above will be given consideration. Other Skills and Abilities: Ability to coordinate priorities and exercise appropriate judgment and discretion. Knowledge of a variety of software; i.e., Microsoft Office applications, Enterprise Platforms, Raisers Edge, Navision, Ceres, HRIS, etc. Project management ability. Knowledge of inventory control for the purpose of ensuring that necessary equipment and replacement parts are always on hand. Ability to interact professionally and effectively with all levels of management, staff and external clients. May be required to come in during nights, weekends or holidays if an operational emergency occurs. Technical/Computer Skills: Minimum of 5 years hands-on Windows Server Administration experience which encompasses maintaining a Microsoft Infrastructure (Active Directory domains, DNS, DHCP, File Sharing and Permissions, Group Policies, etc.). Minimum of 5 years hands-on network management experience. Minimum of 2 years supporting virtualization and working in Public Cloud Infrastructures (Azure, AWS, etc.). Experience supporting security infrastructure - firewalls, IPS/IDS, VPN, and monitoring tools. Experience with VOIP Telephone System Management. Experience managing Microsoft Office 365 environments. Strong project management skills. Gallagher, Flynn, & Company, LLP has been retained to conduct this search. Interested candidates may apply by sending a resume and cover letter to Dan Lyons, Director of HR Consulting or call 802-556-1167. While we appreciate all interest in this opportunity, only candidates most closely aligned with our search will be contacted. Disclaimer: What\u2019s listed above is representative of the responsibilities of the position but are not meant to be an exhaustive list. Responsibilities may change during employment at the company\u2019s discretion. Vermont Foodbank does not discriminate in employment based on race, color, religion, sex (including pregnancy and gender identity), national origin, political affiliation, sexual orientation, marital status, disability, genetic information, age, membership in an employee organization, retaliation, parental status, military service, or other non-merit factor. Job Type: Full-time Pay: $70,000.00 per year Experience: Windows Server Administration: 5 years (Preferred) Network Management: 5 years (Preferred) Education: Bachelor's (Preferred) ",
